title: Feels footsteps through floor
content:
“You both stay here,” said Vashta, “while I try to salvage the situation
out there, and engineer a way for you to continue your investigation!”

“Understood, ma’am,” said Ana.

With one last glare, Vashta turned, flung open the door, charged
through, and slammed it behind her.

[...]

To my surprise, her grin didn’t flicker one jot. “That’s not entirely true,
either.”

“What’s not? That it was the Hazas, or that your assistant was killed?”
“Focus, Din. We are here to figure out how this calamity happened and
who is responsible. Follow that thread, and that thread alone, and we shall
have victory.” Then she cocked her head, knelt, and felt the fretvine floor.
“Vashta is coming back. I can feel her stride in the very wood… And I think
Miljin and Strovi are with her. Come. Let us pretend to be professional, you
and I, for hell and the gentry await.”

“HERE,” SAID VASHTA coldly, “is what I have been able to salvage. First,
Fayazi Haza does not wish to be in the room with you anymore, Immunis.
To have made such an attack on her character during such a period of grief
is beyond toleration. Is that clear?”

Ana shrugged. “That is clear if not welcome, ma’am.”

- The Tainted Cup, Chapter 25 pgs. 219 & 222

title: Reads desk where letter was written
content:
“I can’t find a damn thing,” said Kalista around her pipe. Her breath
shivered with smoke as she spoke. “This is a professional, surely. They
removed everything of note. From the look of it, I almost doubt if Suberek
knew how to write.”

Ana rocked forward, her hands still probing the workshop table. “No,”
she said softly. “He knew how to write. And he did a lot of it right here.”
There was a long silence as everyone turned to look at her, her hands
placed on the slab of wood like a reedwitch telling fortunes at a canton fair.

“You…” Kalista laughed, incredulous. “You aren’t suggesting you
can…You can, what, feel what was written there?”

“I can feel many things,” said Ana quietly. “He was a very hard writer,
you see. Pressed his ashpen with tremendous force…The tricky thing is
identifying what was recent.” Her index finger paused on one spot of the
scarred table. “Here, for example…Wrote down an order for two panels…
Dated sometime in the month of Hajnal. I think. Tricky to read this…”
Uhad looked to Nusis. “Is this really possible?”

“Of course,” said Nusis. “I know some sensitivity grafts help sculptors
and surgeons find the weaknesses in many materials.”

“If we get a length of ashpen,” said Ana, “and a sheet of thin fernpaper,
I can discover more.”

- The Tainted Cup, Chapter 22 pg. 197

title: Reads city's construction orders in three hours
content:
I looked down. Ana was lying on the floor on her back at Strovi’s feet,
half-concealed in a pile of parchments, blindfolded as usual. To her left was
a tray containing the remains of a fish, salted and piled with herbs, the flesh
so pink it must have never known flame.

[...]

“He’s just brought you your orders, ma’am?” I asked. “From the shape
of things, he’s been here awhile. You’ve been interrogating him, haven’t
you.”

“It, ah…” Strovi cleared his throat. “It has been an hour or so, ma’am.
Possibly two. Or, ah, three.”

Ana waved a hand, indifferent. “Possibly. It’s not very often that I get to
parley with a Talagray Legion officer.”

[...]

We possibly have a who. Kind of think we have a how—--for, presumably, 
Jolgalgan came to one of these secret meetings of Engineers and poisoned them 
all there. And thanks to your and Miljin’s work yesterday, Din, we also have a when
---the Engineers were poisoned eight days before the breach, the date of their last
meeting, the sixth of Kyuz. Now we just need the where. And Strovi here has already 
given us the materials we need to solve the rest!” 

She turned her blindfolded face to him. 

“These orders are from every fernpaper miller in the city, correct, Captain?”

“Yes, ma’am,” said Strovi. “All we could find.”

“And we’re looking for big orders. All conducted on or about eight days
before the breach—the day of the poisoning.” She pursed her mouth,
chewing on an especially tough piece of gristle, then said, “There are, I
think, four options.”

Strovi looked startled. “Y-you’ve already read them all, ma’am?”

“Our conversation was interesting, Captain,” she said. “But not so
interesting as to occupy the whole of my attention…” Still blindfolded, she
snatched up four different papers, walked over on her knees, fumbled to
find Strovi’s legs, and then stuffed the papers into his lap. Then she leaned
forward to search the top one with her fingers until she pointed to a line.
“This mill here—Ostrok’s? See it? Order for four panels, nine days before
the breach.”

- The Tainted Cup, Chapter 19 pgs. 171-174

title: Feels weather through floor
content:
“Why are you…” I said.

“On the floor?” she said. “I can feel the movements of this tower better
from here, Din, reading the wind and the weather with my back.” She
grinned. “It’s marvelous. You ought to try it sometime.”

- The Tainted Cup, Chapter 19 pg. 171

title: ffix_playthrough
content:
Final Fantasy IX mostly complete playthrough

Goals:
- See as much content as possible
- Get most unique items 
- Do as many sidequests as possible
- Become the Tetra Master
- Encounter most/all monsters
- Defeat Ozma, which I've never done

Using the following mods:
- ATB mod. Ups the frame rate, speeds up battle intro, and changes the ATB system. We'll see if this is good or not, if it's bad we'll flush it, but we'll probably keep it (https://www.romhacking.net/hacks/9029/)
- Toggle encounters on/off. Generally I'll clear an area first before I allow doing this, exceptions include world map
- Excalibur II 500 hour patch. I'd be fine without the weapon, but why not. An alternative to keeping your game on for 2.25 years to overflow the clock

I'm playing the PSX version. It's on emulator. Don't be annoying about it. Some timing games like jump rope and nobles might not be happening (especially on emu), I'm washed

This is ultimately a replay but it's been a very long time since I've really dug deep into this game. This time I want to play a little more thoroughly with some informed gameplay, like managing stats (https://web.archive.org/web/20250501000000*/http://letao.is-a-geek.net/ff9stats/), but nothing too crazy. It's for fun. I'll definitely miss some random things, who cares. 

Let's play some cards

title: sql_PHP-INSERT-TRY-CATCH-ERRORS
content:
<?php

// Assume $pdo is a PDO connection with ERRMODE_EXCEPTION enabled.

try {

    // Prepare the INSERT
    $stmt = $pdo->prepare("
        INSERT INTO eng_events.`260227_ais_workshop_registration`
            (full_name, email, affiliation, phone)
        VALUES
            (:full_name, :email, :affiliation, :phone)
    ");

    // Bind parameters
    $stmt->execute([
        ':full_name'   => $_POST['full_name'],
        ':email'       => $_POST['email'],
        ':affiliation' => $_POST['affiliation'],
        ':phone'       => $_POST['phone']
    ]);

    // If we reach this point, the INSERT succeeded
    echo "Thank you for your submission.";

} catch (PDOException $e) {

    // SQLSTATE 23000 = integrity constraint violation
    if ($e->getCode() === '23000') {

        // You can inspect $e->getMessage() to map specific constraints
        // to specific user-friendly messages if you want.
        // Example:
        if (strpos($e->getMessage(), 'chk_affiliation') !== false) {
            echo "Your submission was not recorded. Please choose a valid affiliation.";
            exit;
        }

        if (strpos($e->getMessage(), 'chk_email') !== false) {
            echo "Your submission was not recorded. Please enter a valid email address.";
            exit;
        }

        // Fallback for any other constraint violation
        echo "Your submission was not recorded. Please review your entries and try again.";
        exit;
    }

    // Any other database error
    echo "A system error occurred. Please try again later.";
    exit;
}

?>

title: Yu-Gi-Oh! Forbidden Memories: 100% Run - FAQ
content:
Q: What are you trying to do?
A: This is a 100% Speedrun of the game Yu-Gi-Oh! Forbidden Memories. To complete the category, I have to obtain 689 out of 722 cards. Additionally, I have to unlock every duelist in the game. Beating every duelist in Free Duel, however, is not required, so I do not have to do Duel Master K.
 
Q: How come it's 689 instead of 722? What about the other 33?
A: The 33 cards in this game are either completely unobtainable or just unreasonable to obtain, as two of the cards do not even have a password (Black Magic Ritual and Magician of Black Chaos), while the rest of the cards require the Maximum amount of Starchips to buy. (That amount being 999,999 Starchips).
 
Q: What are you playing on?
A: ePSXe 1.9.0, an emulator created for PlayStation [1] games.
 
Q: Is this run done in one segment?
A: It is not. As an average 100% run would take anywhere between 75 to 90 hours, it is unrealistic to complete the run as RTA, so Real Time is irrelevant; as such, pausing the timer is allowed - which is understandable as it otherwise can be very health damaging. Runners normally spend time between segments checking to see what cards they're missing and what would be their next farming option, which greatly reduces farming, but the rules do not say to count this extra time.
 
Q: What is the World Record?
A: 66:58:45 by gui93.
 
Q: How do you get a card into your library?
A: By winning the card, buying it, Fusing for it, or Ritual Summoning it. Most cards are won, but some can only be Fused for or Ritual Summoned. Notably, some cards are also starchip only cards, one of which is Seiyaryu, costing 1,700 starchips.
 
Q: What route do you use?
A: This spreadsheet might be of use to you: https://docs.google.com/spreadsheets/d/1Rxb9WJmgYjwXg_Tw_0Vt6OvITb-yepq_EinKtSVZTHI/edit?gid=209307858#gid=209307858
 
Q: Is it possible to do every Ritual in the game?
A: Sadly, no. You cannot perform Javelin Beetle Pact and Resurrection of Chakra due to Hercules Beetle and Dark Artist being maximum Starchips. The Ritual Magics themselves can be bought or fused.
 
Q: What cards are unobtainable?
A: https://pastebin.com/Lt3ZYdW5 - Although that pastebin lists all of those cards as unobtainable, if you look at the spreadsheet, the cards which are filled as red you cannot obtain in this category.
